<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

<p class="updated">
Last Updated: July 1, 2026
</p>

<p>
This Privacy Policy explains how the <strong>SHREE RCH Extension</strong> collects, uses, stores, and protects information while using the extension.
</p>

<h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>

<p>The extension may collect the following information:</p>

<ul>
<li>Google account email address (for authentication).</li>
<li>RCH ID entered by the user.</li>
<li>Mobile number entered for activation.</li>
<li>Payment reference (UTR) submitted during activation.</li>
<li>Extension settings and preferences stored locally.</li>
</ul>

<h2>2. Why We Collect Information</h2>

<ul>
<li>To verify your subscription.</li>
<li>To activate your account.</li>
<li>To provide extension functionality.</li>
<li>To prevent unauthorized access.</li>
<li>To improve the extension.</li>
</ul>

<h2>3. Chrome Permissions</h2>

<p>
The extension requests only the permissions required for its functionality, including:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Identity (Google Sign-In)</li>
<li>Storage</li>
<li>Notifications</li>
<li>Host permissions required for the RCH portal</li>
</ul>

<h2>4. Data Storage</h2>

<p>
Some settings are stored using Chrome Storage for faster operation. Authentication and account activation data may be securely verified using our backend services.
</p>

<h2>5. Data Sharing</h2>

<p>
We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal information.
Information is only used to provide extension services and account verification.
</p>

<h2>6. Security</h2>

<p>
Reasonable technical measures are used to protect user information from unauthorized access or misuse.
</p>

<h2>7. Third-Party Services</h2>

<p>
The extension may interact with services such as:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Google Authentication</li>
<li>Firebase</li>
<li>Government RCH Portal</li>
</ul>

<p>
These services operate under their own privacy policies.
</p>

<h2>8. Changes to this Policy</h2>

<p>
We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. The updated version will always be available on this page.
</p>

